  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Occasionally, an item will be defective during initial inspection upon receiving the item into your inventory or after an installation. A Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) is a part of the Reverse Logistics cycle, where defective products are returned to the manufacturer or vendor during the warranty period. If you process all of your RMA items at a central location, you can bulk-edit these items to the location assigned for processing.</p><h3 id=\"RMAProcess:TransferringRMAstoaCentralLocationforProcessing-NextStep\">Next Step</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932296378/RMA+Process+Sending+RMA+Items+to+the+Supplier+RMA+Batch\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932296378\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Sending RMA Items to the Supplier (RMA Batch)</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"RMAProcess:TransferringRMAstoaCentralLocationforProcessing-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525631/Return+Merchandise+Authorization+RMA+Tracking+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525631\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) Tracking Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932460163/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+From+a+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932460163\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA From a Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931116776/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+Through+Inventory+Fulfillment\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931116776\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA Through Inventory Fulfillment</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934721039/Reports+Inventory+Usage\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934721039\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Inventory Usage</a>\u00a0- Detail Reporting for RMA Credit/RMA Rejected/Shrinkage</p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931018445/Inventory+Management+Adjust+Inventory+Levels+via+Import\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931018445\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Management: Updating Inventory Attributes in Bulk</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"RMAProcess:TransferringRMAstoaCentralLocationforProcessing-Bulk-EditRMAItemstoaNewLocation\">Bulk-Edit RMA Items to a New Location</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Inventory</strong> \u2192 <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Detail</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"453\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/RMA%20Location%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Inventory Detail List, filter your search results to <strong>Inventory Process: RMA Process</strong>. Any items that are in Pending RMA status will show on the list.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/RMA%20Location%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: By default, results will only show for the last 90 days. You may need to set the Date Range filter for All Time if there are items that have aged past that time period.</p><p /><p>3. From the list of results, use the checkboxes to select the item(s) that you would like to transfer to another location. After you have made your selection(s) click the <strong>Edit Selected button</strong>. From the list of options, click <strong>Edit Selected</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/RMA%20Location%203.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/RMA%20Location%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. A Bulk Edit pop-up will appear. Update the Attribute field to <strong>Location</strong>, and update the New Value field to the location you are transferring the items. Add any additional notes, if necessary. When you are satisfied with your changes, click <strong>Apply</strong> to update the inventory items.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932198033/RMA%20Location%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. At this point, the items have been updated in the system as assigned to the new location, and you will need to send those items to that target location.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
